Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @corn on the cob{2} widthways by running a #knife{} firmly around the middle, then snapping them in half with your hands.

Pop the corn onto a large sheet of #foil{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you'd like, then scrunch the foil closed to create a parcel.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the corn is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

While the corn roasts, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and @green pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips). Discard the core and seeds.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and fry, stirring occasionally, until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Set aside once softened.

Meanwhile, combine the @tomato puree{30%g}, @Mexican style spice mix{1%tbsp} and olive oil for the topping in a #small bowl{}.

> TIP: Add less spice if you prefer things milder.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}(grated).

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} (2 per person) onto a #baking tray{} and cover with the tomato puree mixture, leaving a 1cm border around the edge.

When the peppers are cooked, scatter them over the tortizza bases and sprinkle the cheese all over - start from the centre outwards to make the 'supernova' explosion!

Bake your tortizzas on the middle shelf of your oven until the base is golden and the cheese is bubbling, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> Space Ranger Mission: Supernova spotted! Little space rangers can help scatter the cheese over the tortizza bases to make the explosions. You'll add the explosion cores when serving.

Once the corn is cooked, carefully remove from the foil and spread with a little @?butter{} if you'd like.

When ready, transfer the fajita 'supernova' tortizzas to your plates and top with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{100%g} to make your explosion cores.

Serve with the corn on the cob alongside. Enjoy!